reviewText: Honestly, this is my favorite stand-up show I have ever seen. I've watched it too many times to count. The songs he makes are witty and clever and smart and stupid and existential all at the same time. He makes you sad, laugh, and think about your existence all in the same song and it's just wonderful. Bo Burnham is a gift to the world. If you like George Carlin, Dane Cook, Daniel Tosh, or any other comedians that aren't scared to joke about dark subject matter, than you'll love Bo. He does what so many great comedians do, and at the same time he puts a lot of it in song, which to me is a maaaaajor plus. I would definitely suggest Bo to everyone.

reviewText: Bo Burnham has come a long way from uploading funny and punny songs from his bedroom on YouTube. In this special, Bo really lets his nerd flag fly.  He ups his game.  He goes beyond the singing comedian shtick.  He has definitely put his comedic lyrical skills to great use, not just in the songs and raps, but also in sonnets and haikus.  And if "Oh Bo" is not stuck in your head by the time the special ends, you are devoid of life!

reviewText: Bo Burnham offers a lot of one liners, snappy comebacks, well thought out stories and puns. It's a great comedy routine for any adult who is tired of all the "Git 'R Done" type comedians that seem to be polluting stand-up comedy.
